Are you flexible, willing to travel, and are comfortable with IT and Customer Support?
Are you well-spoken, do you know how to manage a variety of projects and are self-starting?
Are you able to think analytically, do you have excellent communication skills, and can work with multiple stakeholders in different time zones and countries?
Who is ABS?

ABS Laundry Business Solutions, established in 1987, is a consultancy firm specialised in developing and implementing software solutions for Industrial Laundries.

Today ABS is the world market leader and employs over 150 dedicated employees located across the globe in The Netherlands (head office), America, Japan, France, Romania, Belgium, Germany, United Kingdom, Denmark and Spain. Our software has developed into a comprehensive and integrated Industrial Laundry Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) & Contract Management solution, which incorporates the latest technologies to deliver intuitive solutions for multi and single plant organizations.

Job Description

As a Business Consultant Trainee, you will have the opportunity to learn within our global company and develop professionally to become a Business Consultant. It is a full-time position, combining work and professional training. During the traineeship, you will work with different departments and projects within ABS. You will be paired with a colleague or manager.

Although it is a traineeship, you will have the responsibilities and salary associated with an entry level position.

You will be based in Plymouth, Minnesota, and start with a training program that includes time at our head office in The Netherlands. Part of your job may include travel to customers throughout the US and Canada.

A strong affinity with ICT and familiarity with logistic business processes is important. Knowledge of project management skills (e.g. Prince2 or PMP) is an advantage, as is knowledge of the laundry business.

Besides being able to think analytically, you have to be service orientated and strive for excellence. This position requires willingness to travel. Occasional weekend work is expected.

Most important required competencies
Flexibility;
Accurate;
Inventive;
Stress-resistant;
Customer-oriented attitude.
After the traineeship

After successfully completing the traineeship, you are a Business Consultant and as such responsible for the preparation, execution and management of projects all over the world. You are the face of the organization and you lead the conversations with the customer. You are the first point of contact, from the sale until the full implementation of our software applications. The implementations are of course supported by an internal organisation with various disciplines.

Tasks & Responsibilities

During the traineeship you will learn the various departments and activities of ABS and will grow towards the job Business Consultant with the following tasks & responsibilities:
Drafting and managing a full implementation plan;
Follow-up to the actions drawn up in the project plan and ensure/monitor a timely completion;
Identifying and tracing possible escalations and informing (project) management;
Guiding the installation of software and hardware;
Supervising and following up on data migration until fully completed;
Defining possible gaps and working out functional designs;
Providing application training to the customer (end users) so that the customer can work with the new software (and hardware);
Creation of reports after customer visits and follow-up on the actions resulting from them;
Create customized user manuals and process descriptions;
Testing and documenting newly developed software;
Acting as a sounding board for clients as a professional consultant;
Monitoring of reported problems and informing customers about the status and details;
Account management activities to ensure healthy, long term relationship with customers.
What we offer

We offer a full-time, salaried position with a customized benefits package, tailored to your work experience and training. In addition to excellent working conditions, we offer you the opportunity to develop yourself within our company.

