Project Management: 1 year (Preferred)
Required travel:
25% (Preferred)

New Albany-based Exhibitpro, a full-service exhibit house, is seeking a full-time Assistant Project Manager to join our team.

The successful candidate will support our Project Management and Business Development teams to consistently achieve client satisfaction from planning through production and completion, while meeting client deadlines and budgets.

· Analyzes project requirements from client and/or sales team; understands and defines project scope; and communicates pertinent details of deliverables and deadlines to relevant parties;

· Coordinates work across teams and facilitates information between client and internal staff to manage the project, make necessary decisions and ensure successful completion and client satisfaction;

· Submits purchase requisitions to purchasing for any required materials or services;

· Identifies show services requirements; works with internal staff to produce show budgets; obtains client approval of budget; authorizes show service orders; and ensures timely, accurate delivery of ordered services;

· Schedules and participates in pre-production meetings to drive production launch and ensure design and production teams have received the necessary information to execute the project on schedule and within budget;

· Facilitates and participates in relevant project meetings to resolve any problems, answer any questions, and clarify any issues as well as communicate any changes in deadlines or scope;

· Schedules and facilitates client previews, as necessary;

· Prepares completed projects for billing;

Requirements include:

· Education: Associate's degree (minimum); Bachelor's degree (preferred)

· Experience: This is an entry level position

· Must have customer-centric attitude, dedicated to providing client-focused solutions

· Must have excellent communication, time management and organizational skills

· Ability to anticipate problems, analyze and proactively determine alternate solutions

· Must be accurate and detail-oriented

· Strong interpersonal skills with emphasis on relationship building

· Ability to work flexible hours and operate under severe time constraints

About Exhibitpro:

· Since 1991, Exhibitpro has delivered successful face-to-face marketing solutions with trade show exhibits, event management and branded corporate environments. Our state-of-the-art production facility and award-winning showroom serve as modern idea labs to inspire your vision. Our team works with each client to provide a tailored marketing solution for their specific objectives. Exhibitpro provides comprehensive trade show services, from strategy development to dynamic and creative exhibit creation. Exhibitpro is a nationally certified woman-owned business.

Job Description
Framework Solutions, a growing company serving the project management needs of pharmaceutical companies nationwide, is currently seeking candidates for the Client Process Manager position located in our new Cincinnati office. We are in Inc 5000 company, that values our associates with competitive wages, a full benefits plan, paid time off, training, and performance bonuses. We are recognized in the Pharmaceutical industry for the great work we do, and are viewed as a valuable part of their ability to bring products to the consumer market more efficiently.

Your responsibilities as a Client Process Manager will include:
Managing the progress of marketing projects through an FDA-regulated review and approval process;
Participating in live meetings with legal, medical and regulatory professionals on a weekly basis;
Arranging regular and ad-hoc meetings to assess the compliance of marketing projects with company standards and FDA regulations;
Prioritizing project reviews in collaboration with client representatives;
Managing projects through a regulated process using process / document management software applications; and
Analyzing processes to identify opportunities for improvement.
Please contact us if you:
Are organized;
Have excellent communication skills;
Pay close attention to detail;
Excel at time management; and
Have an aptitude for building professional working relationships with clients.
Bachelor's Degree required.
Company Description
Framework Solutions, Inc. is a fast growing company and a member of the INC 5000 for two consecutive years and counting.
